translated: Lundell, Nils Erik Gunnar, hospital physician, Kungälv, born on May 13th, 1901 in Tångeråsa, Örebro County, the son of primary school teacher Alvar L. and Elin Sandvall. Married in 1935 to Åslög Ejvinsdotter. Children: Anders, born in 1936. Completed high school in Örebro in 1919, obtained a Bachelor of Medicine degree in 1924, and a medical license in 1929 in Uppsala. Worked as a medical assistant at Sätra Sanatorium from 1926, assistant physician at the municipal hospital in Eksjö from 1928, surgical department at Uppsala University Hospital from 1929, resident and acting deputy physician at the surgical department of Sundsvall County Hospital from 1929 to 1931, third and second deputy physician at the surgical department of Karlstad County Hospital from 1931 to 1932, second deputy physician at the surgical department of Stocksund County Hospital from 1933 to 1934, acting deputy physician at the surgical department of Sabbatsbergs Hospital from 1934, first deputy physician in Karlstad from 1935 to 1938, temporarily there in 1938, assistant medical officer at Sabbatsbergs Hospital Ear Clinic in the same year, deputy physician at Sahlgrenska Hospital surgical department in 1939, and hospital physician in Kungälv since 1943.
